LAGOS – Honourable Ganiyu Johnson,  lawmaker representing Oshodi/Isolo Federal Constituency 2, at the green chamber of the National Assembly has congratulated Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and a presidential aspirant in the just concluded party’s primary election, over his emergence as the party’s flag bearer in 2023 general elections. Johnson noted that the party’s delegates made the right choice by electing the man with the experience, leadership quality, political structure to win the forthcoming presidential election for the APC, even as he hailed other aspirants who stepped down for Asiwaju, in the rancour-free election, stressing that they have indeed set the pace for greater achievements. The lawmaker in a press statement signed by his media aide, Dotun Oladapo, expressed confidence in Asiwaju’s capability and vast experience in steering this nation to her intended destination. “This is a new dawn in our political history and the beginning of a new thing to come. The capability of Asiwaju to provide needed leadership that would lead the nation to accomplish her glory is not in doubt. “I salute and doff my hat for those who fought for the ticket with Asiwaju but who considered it imperative in the spirit of sportsmanship to withdraw before the contest started. You shall all be remembered for good in the history of our party and our great country” the statement reads. The former Lagos State Commissioner for Works and Infrastructure also extended his appreciation to all the delegates and the party leadership for the peaceful conduct of the election, pointing out that he is optimist that Asiwaju Bola Tinubu will use his vast experience to bring political, socio-economic and security challenges to a halt, even as he commended President Muhamnafu Buhari for leading by example and ensuring that democracy was given a chance to play out during the election process.